                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">1. Using the Get Information About Pupils (GIAP) website</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    Please read these terms of use carefully before using this website. We recommend that you keep a copy for your records.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    GIAP contains highly sensitive personal information about pupils in schools and colleges. It is your responsibility to ensure that any personal data or sensitive personal data you access in GIAP cannot be viewed or used by any unauthorised persons. Your username and password are specific to you and must not be shared with any other person.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="TOC2">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">2. Get Information About Pupils (GIAP) Website Terms of Use</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    The GIAP website is operated by the <strong>Department for Education</strong> ('<strong>DfE</strong>, <strong>we</strong>
                    or <strong>us</strong>').
                    These terms of use apply to all and authorised users of the GIAP website ('<strong>you</strong>').
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    In these terms of use, the following definitions apply:
                </p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>
                        '<strong>approver</strong>' means an authorised user within an organisation, with additional
                        responsibilities for GIAP, including checking and verifying proposed authorised users' suitability
                        for access; and set-up, administration and deletion of authorised users' GIAP accounts
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        '<strong>authorised user</strong>' means a person authorised to use GIAP, with a unique active
                        username that is linked to him/her within GIAP, working for the organisation to which the username
                        is issued
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        '<strong>data controller</strong>' has the meaning given to it in the General Data Protection
                        Regulation (GDPR) and the Data Protection Act (DPA) 2018. DfE is the data controller in relation to
                        the personal data and the sensitive personal data held in the GIAP website
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        '<strong>data subject</strong>' means the living individual who is the subject of the personal data
                        or the sensitive personal data
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        '<strong>personal data</strong>' means data about a living individual who can be identified from
                        that data or from that data and other information which is in, or likely to come into, the data
                        controller's possession.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        '<strong>processing</strong>' has the meaning set out in GDPR and the DPA 2018 and in
                        relation to personal data, means obtaining, recording or holding the information or data or
                        carrying out any operation or set of operations on the information or data, including:
                        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                            <li>
                                organisation, adaptation or alteration of the information or data
                            </li>
                            <li>retrieval, consultation or use of the information or data</li>
                            <li>
                                disclosure of the information or data by transmission, dissemination or otherwise
                                making available
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                alignment, combination, blocking, erasure or destruction of the information or data
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>'protected data'</strong> means any personal data and/or any sensitive personal data and any
                        data derived from it in any form such as text, drawings, diagrams, images or sounds (together with
                        any database made up of any of these) which are embodied in any electronic, magnetic, optical or
                        tangible media.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

