            <div id="TOC5">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">5. Accessing the GIAP website - authorised users and approvers</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">You must treat your username, password or other information issued to you as part of our security procedures as confidential and not disclose it to a third party.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    You <strong>must</strong>:
                </p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>comply with the password guidance at registration</li>
                    <li>
                        change your password on a regular basis and whenever there is any indication of possible system
                        or password compromise
                    </li>
                    <li>only connect to the GIAP website using a secured internet connection</li>
                    <li>
                        ensure screens on devices accessing GIAP outside the workplace cannot be read by other people
                    </li>
                    <li>ensure you log-off GIAP after completing your session.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    You must not allow anyone else to use your username and password to access GIAP or:
                </p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>
                        keep a record (e.g. paper, software file or PDA) of your username and password, unless this can
                        be stored securely in accordance with government standards
                    </li>
                    <li>include passwords in any automated log-on processor</li>
                    <li>access personal data or sensitive personal data in GIAP from outside the UK</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    We have the right to disable any username or password, whether chosen by you or allocated by us/an
                    approver, at any time, if in our reasonable opinion you have failed to comply with any of these terms of
                    use. If you know or suspect that anyone other than you knows your username or password, you must
                    promptly notify us using the
                    <a id="termsofuse--sign-in-help--link" href="https://help.signin.education.gov.uk/contact" class="govuk-link" target="_blank">
                        DfE Sign-in Help
                    </a> page.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    If you are an approver, you accept responsibility for the secure management of GIAP usernames within
                    your organisation and for ensuring your organisation has appropriate security measures in place to
                    protect personal data and sensitive personal data accessed in GIAP.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    You <strong>must</strong> comply with the conditions below:
                </p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>
                        ensure that identity and other appropriate checks have been made on an individual before
                        issuing a username and password, including checking a person's suitability to access children's
                        personal data and sensitive personal data
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        only issue a non-transferable username and password that is linked to an individual authorised
                        user and transmit these to the authorised user in a secure manner
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        check the identity of authorised users before resetting passwords
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        ensure authorised users receive appropriate data protection and information security awareness
                        training and regular updates
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        ensure that on termination of employment an authorised user's username is removed from the
                        GIAP system and verify that the authorised user no longer retains any personal data or sensitive
                        personal data obtained from GIAP
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        review the list of usernames under your control every three months to ensure that the list
                        does not contain names that should have been removed
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        inform the GIAP helpdesk of any suspected security incident that may compromise GIAP as soon as
                        is practically possible.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="govuk-body">You <strong> must never</strong>:</p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>
                        ask authorised users to disclose passwords; or send unsolicited emails to authorised users
                        asking them to logon to GIAP
                    </li>
                    <li>recycle a username or password</li>
                    <li>transfer your approver privileges to another authorised user</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    Help of this can be found at:
                    <br>
                    <a id="termsofuse--sign-in-approver--link" href="https://help.signin.education.gov.uk/contact/approver" class="govuk-link" target="_blank">
                        https://help.signin.education.gov.uk/contact/approver
                    </a>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="TOC6">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">6. Using and sharing personal data and sensitive personal data from GIAP</h2>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>
                        GIAP contains personal data and sensitive personal data about pupils in schools and colleges.
                        You must ensure that any personal data and any sensitive personal data you access in GIAP cannot
                        be viewed or used by any unauthorised persons.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        you agree to comply with data protection and privacy laws including, but not limited to, the
                        Data Protection Act 2018 and GDPR, where they apply in relation to personal data and sensitive
                        personal data processed in connection with GIAP.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        you agree only to use the personal data and sensitive personal data you access in GIAP for
                        lawful educational purposes, in the interests of individual pupils and not for any other
                        purpose. You are only permitted to share personal data and sensitive personal data from GIAP
                        with those who you are satisfied need the data to discharge a statutory education function.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        you must not retain personal data from GIAP on local authorities' systems, or on electronic or
                        paper-based records, for pupils who are not on the roll of schools within your local authority.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        you must not retain personal data from GIAP on local authorities’ systems, or on electronic or paper-based records, for pupils for which you have no statutory responsibility (i.e. children not on the roll of a school within your authority).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        you must not print, save, or record in any way, any html pages from the GIAP website that
                        contain pupil-specific information. This restriction does not apply to PDF/XLS/CSV/CTF/Tab files
                        that are downloaded from GIAP.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        if you are not an authorised user, you must not access or try to access personal data or
                        sensitive personal data held in GIAP <strong>by any method</strong>. This does not limit your rights, if
                        applicable, as a data subject under the DPA 2018 and GDPR.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        data protections laws should never be used as an excuse for failure to protect a child from a
                        real risk of harm. For further information see:
                        <a id="termsofuse--safeguarding-practitioners-information--link" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/safeguarding-practitioners-information-sharing-advice">
                            https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/safeguarding-practitioners-information-sharing-advice
                        </a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

