                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">11. Viruses, hacking and other offences</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    When using GIAP, you must not introduce viruses, trojans, worms, logic bombs or any other material that's malicious or technologically harmful.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    You must not try to gain unauthorised access to GIAP, the server on which it's stored, or any server, computer or database connected to it.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    You must not attack GIAP in any way. This includes denial-of-service attacks.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    We'll report any attacks or attempts to gain unauthorised access to GIAP to the relevant law enforcement authorities and share information about you with them.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="TOC12">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">12. Hoax messages and phishing</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    DfE, local authorities, multi-academy trusts or school approvers will never send an unsolicited email to you asking you to log-on to GIAP or ask for your password. You must not respond to such a request. If you receive such a request, please report it to your approver who should then report it to us.
                </p>
