            <div id="TOC17">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">17. System access levels</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    The GIAP system is available to:
                </p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>local authorities - full access</li>
                    <li>multi-academy trusts – full access</li>
                    <li>single-academy trusts - full access</li>
                    <li>local authority maintained schools – standard access</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    Local authority maintained schools have standard access (as MATs and SATs have additional responsibilities that do not apply to maintained schools) and will need to contact their LA for some LA responsibility features of the system.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    FE colleges and Post-16 schools have the same level of access as maintained schools.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    Access for establishments (‘establishments’ excludes LAs and MATs) is also regulated by the age range of the establishment.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="TOC18">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">18. Non-UPN searches</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">Where an establishment / organisation is to search for a pupil using the non-UPN search function, it can only be used to search for a pupil that <strong>has joined or is going to join the establishment</strong>.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
                    There is no other scenario to search for a pupil using the non-UPN search. The pupil must have joined or be about to join the establishment / organisation without UPN details.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body">
